<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY-AREA ROUNDUP; MILLER LIFTS WESTLAKE INTO TIE FOR FIRST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Westlake High forward Billy Miller scored six of his 14 points during the 
third quarter Monday night to break open a tight Marmonte League game and give 
the host Warriors a 62-53 win over Agoura and move them into a first-place tie 
with the Chargers and Thousand Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake (15-5, 9-3 in league play) outscored Agoura (15-5, 9-3), 20-8, in the 
third quarter.Sophomore Steve Aylsworth of Westlake scored a game-high 20 
points. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley 72, Royal 61 -- Stuart Clarke, Nathan Simmons and Vernon Simmons 
each scored 13 points for the Pioneers (16-7, 7-4) in a Marmonte League game at 
Royal. 
</P>
<P>
 North Hollywood 87, Sherman Oaks CES 52 -- Damon Ollie scored 28 points and 
grabbed 17 rebounds as the Huskies remained undefeated in the Valley Pac-8 
Conference. 
</P>
<P>
 Birmingham 63, Monroe 59 -- Birmingham junior Scott James scored 15 points and 
Marc Fernando added 13 in Valley Pac-8 Conference game at Birmingham (6-10, 
3-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Notre Dame 80, St. Bernard 57 -- Knight guard Tommy Zapata scored 22 of his 
game-high 28 points in the second half in a Mission League game. 
</P>
<P>
 Grant 71, Canoga Park 60 -- Ron Patterson scored 25 points for the Lancers in 
a Valley Pac-8 Conference game. 
</P>
<P>
 Poly 72, Sylmar 66 -- The Parrots rallied from a third-quarter, 17-point 
deficit using a full-court press in a Valley Pac-8 Conference game. GIRLS' 
BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Alemany 49, Harvard-Westlake 27 -- Sophomore Carly Funicello scored 17 points 
and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead the Indians in a Mission League game. Samantha 
Rigley and Kelly McKay added 11 points each for Alemany (22-0, 11-0), who 
clinched the Mission League championship. 
</P>
