<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY-AREA DIGEST: BELL-JEFF BASKETBALL COACH TO QUIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Citing frustration with the athletes and athletic department at Bell-Jeff 
High, basketball Coach Steve Wahl said Monday he will not coach at the school 
after this season. Wahl resigned as the school's baseball coach in December. 
</P>
<P>
 "There is a difference in philosophy with me and the school and particularly 
the athletic department," said Wahl, whose team is 9-13. "I'm a little 
disillusioned with Bell-Jeff athletes. I think I'm working harder than they 
are, and that's wrong. You get to that point and you have to hang it up." 
</P>
<P>
 Wahl has kicked two basketball players off the team, two others have quit, and 
three starters -- Dave Matekel, Anthony Couch and Mike Reyes -- were ruled 
academically ineligible Monday. Of the 14 players Wahl began the season with, 
six remain. 
</P>
<P>
 Wahl, 42, has coached basketball, tennis and baseball at various times for the 
past eight years at Bell-Jeff. JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
