<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: NEW REGENCY PRODUCTIONS NAMES NATHANSON PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As expected, Michael Nathanson on Monday was named president and chief 
executive of Arnon Milchan's New Regency Productions. 
</P>
<P>
 Nathanson, the former worldwide production president at Columbia Pictures, 
will run day-to-day operations at the independent company, which is located on 
the Warner Bros. lot.The company plans to increase its output to as many as 15 
movies a year. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is a great opportunity," Nathanson said. "I now have the comfort of 
being a principal architect in almost 15 pictures a year, without the 
bureaucracy of a big studio system." 
</P>
<P>
 * Rochel Blachman is set to join the business affairs department at Paramount 
Pictures. Also at Paramount, Mark Badagliacca has been named senior vice 
president of planning. 
</P>
<P>
 * Elliot Slutzky has joined Live Entertainment as executive vice president of 
sales and marketing. Jeffrey Fink has been named vice president of sales and 
distribution for Live Home Video. 
</P>
<P>
 * Los Angeles-based Loeb & Loeb has joined the entertainment industry's 
Nashville migration by naming Malcolm Mimms to head its new law office there. 
</P>
<P>
 * Irwin Jacobson has been named director of accounting for Sony Pictures 
Studios. 
</P>
<P>
 * Douglas Bergmann is director of research for the Screen Actors Guild. 
</P>
