<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: TOKYO; HOSOKAWA TO SUMMIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa heads to Washington for a Friday summit 
meeting focused on U.S.-Japanese trade issues, particularly proposed steps to 
further open Japan's markets to foreign goods and services. 
</P>
<P>
 American and Japanese negotiators are trying to reach a set of trade 
agreements in four priority areas before the summit: automobiles and auto 
parts, insurance, telecommunications and medical equipment. Talks have been 
virtually deadlocked by disagreement on whether to include numerical goals to 
measure progress in expanding market access. 
</P>
<P>
 U.S. officials say difficult negotiations are likely to continue up to the 
last possible moment but add that there is a possibility of success. 
</P>
