<P>
 The reason the Houston Rockets rejected a trade for Sean Elliott was because 
the Detroit forward has a lingering kidney infection, the player's agent said. 
</P>
<P>
 Olympic ice dancer Elizabeth Punsalan prepared to bury her father in Lorain, 
Ohio, as her brother pleaded not guilty to aggravated murder in the elder 
Punsalan's death. 
</P>
<P>
 Ricardo Punsalan, 20, waived his right to a preliminary hearing during an 
arraignment before Lorain Municipal Judge Gustalo Nunez. 
</P>
<P>
 Amos Mansdorf of Israel defeated Greg Rusedski of Canada, 7-6 (7-5), 7-6 
(7-3), in the first round of the Muratti Time indoor tennis tournament at 
Milan, Italy. . . . Eva Martinkova of the Czech Republic needed only 63 minutes 
to upset second-seeded Mary Pierce of France, 6-4, 6-1, in the first round at 
Linz, Austria. 
</P>
<P>
 Donovan (Razor) Ruddock and Dan Murphy will not meet in a heavyweight bout on 
Feb. 19 at the Charlotte Coliseum because of Ruddock's emergency tonsillectomy. 
. . . Carlos Gonzalez of Mexico knocked out Steve Larrimore of the Bahamas at 
2:50 of the second round in a junior welterweight bout at the Forum. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael J. Robbie, 45-year-old son of Miami Dolphin founder Joe Robbie, was 
arrested in a drug sting near the stadium named after his father, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The 1994 NBA draft will be held June 29 at the Hoosier Dome in Indianapolis, 
the league announced. 
</P>
