<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: INSURANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Quake Insurance Loss Estimate Released: As expected, the insurance industry 
formally released its estimate that insurance claims from the Northridge 
earthquake will total $2.5 billion.The Property Claim Services division of the 
American Insurance Services Group said the Jan. 17 quake will result in about 
230,000 claims for residential and commercial damage. The estimate does not 
include the far greater cost of destruction to uninsured property, including 
publicly owned infrastructure. Total damage from the earthquake has been 
estimated at as much as $30 billion. 
</P>
