<HEADLINE>
<P>
STUDENT DEFENDS SELF-DEFENSE CLASS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * My photograph was on the front page of the Los Angeles Times because I took 
a self-defense class with the Defense Department. 
</P>
<P>
 I thought it was a great way to learn how to defend yourself.I learned that 
you could set boundaries for yourself if people were too close. I learned 
targets on the body that could injure a person who was trying to do a bad thing 
to me. 
</P>
<P>
 I think other kids should take this class because they should learn how to 
defend themselves. I think my parents were right to send me and my brother to 
this class. 
</P>
<P>
 I think the Los Angeles Times people who wrote the article should have been 
there longer to see what the class really taught kids. 
</P>
<P>
 KYLE MROHS 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge 
