SMALL EFFORT COULD CURB TRASH PROBLEM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * I found the Valley Focus story by Jeff Schnaufer "Merchants Adopting 
Boulevard Medians," (Dec. 28) sad. 
</P>
<P>
 Sad because of the lack of funds enabling the city to perform the task of 
maintenance. 
</P>
<P>
 I feel there is no excuse for trashing any area. People should pick up after 
themselves. With this small effort, the cities could handle eroding maintenance 
at a minimum cost. 
</P>
<P>
 I appreciate all the merchants' efforts to keep streets from unsightly clutter 
and graffiti. This effort truly reflects an owner's care and pride in the 
investment. 
