<P>
EARTHQUAKE: THE LONG ROAD BACK; QUAKE MAGNITUDE UPGRADED TO 6.7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Caltech and the U.S. Geological Survey said Monday that they are upgrading the 
magnitude of the Northridge earthquake from 6.6 to 6.7, based on their analyses 
and the results of digital seismographs from around the world. 
</P>
<P>
 An official announcement of an upgraded magnitude is also expected this week 
from the National Earthquake Information Center in Golden, Colo., a Geological 
Survey spokeswoman said. 
