<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LA CANADA FLINTRIDGE; 
70 ANTI-SEMITIC FLYERS FOUND IN SCHOOL LOCKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Sheriff's Department is investigating the stuffing of 70 anti-Semitic 
flyers into student lockers at two La Canada Flintridge schools over the 
weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 About 40 flyers were found Monday morning at La Canada High School and 30 
flyers were discovered at the Ability Plus School, a private elementary school, 
said sheriff's spokesman George Ducoulombier.The flyers contained caricatures 
of Jews, talked about deadly violence against Jews and listed a telephone 
number. 
</P>
<P>
 James E. Stratton, principal of La Canada High, said the student lockers are 
outside the school buildings and are accessible to anyone who trespasses onto 
the unguarded campus. Stratton said it is impossible to patrol the school 24 
hours a day, but he visited each classroom Monday to express his revulsion at 
the flyers. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is not something that the school in any way condones," Stratton said. 
</P>
