<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOWLING BALL IS DROPPED ON CAR, KILLS BABY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A bowling ball dropped from an overpass slammed through the front window of a 
car and fatally injured an 8-month-old girl. 
</P>
<P>
 The baby, riding in the back seat of the car with her 3-year-old brother, was 
struck in the face Sunday night and died in surgery at a Newark hospital 
Monday, said Ed DeFazio, the first assistant prosecutor in Hudson County. 
</P>
<P>
 The identity of the baby and her family wasn't immediately released. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're not saying someone intended to kill someone, but the level of 
intelligence we're dealing with is amazing," DeFazio said. "It's really tragic. 
We're all very upset about this." 
</P>
<P>
 DeFazio said the bowling ball was dropped from an elevated portion of a 
highway near the Holland Tunnel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
