<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: JOINING THE CLUB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by James M. Gomez, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Candle Subacute Services Inc., a privately owned company in Irvine, has become 
a member of the merger mania club. 
</P>
<P>
 Employees at the small health care contractor will now be getting their 
paychecks from Vencor Inc., a $212-million, Kentucky-based owner and operator 
of hospitals and nursing care facilities for the the chronically ill. 
</P>
<P>
 Vencor, which specializes in treating patients who need long-term life 
support, bought Candle Subacute Services for an undisclosed sum. Candle 
Subacute Services officials declined comment on the deal and Vencor officials 
did not return phone calls. 
</P>
<P>
 Candle Subacute Services has 15 contracts to provide health care services for 
the chronically ill to hospitals and nursing homes throughout Southern 
California. 
