<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. COMPUTER FIRMS ENTER MULTIMEDIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Multimedia computers are in vogue for computer manufacturers looking to boost 
revenues. On Monday, two Orange County computer makers launched low-priced PCs 
that can run multimedia software, which combines text, audio, video and 
graphics in a single presentation. 
</P>
<P>
 Advanced Logic Research Inc. in Irvine said it will sell its Multimedia 
Express computer for $1,995. Meanwhile, Canon Computer Systems Inc. in Costa 
Mesa said it has launched its Innova Vision multimedia desktop computer as well 
as six other computer models. Both companies say their machines sport the 
latest in multimedia equipment, including speakers, CD-ROM drives, monitors and 
sound cards. 
</P>
<P>
 The Innova Vision will sell for an estimated $1,850 to $1,950. Consumers have 
been buying machines with the extra multimedia components in about half of 
their new PC purchases now that prices have tumbled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
