<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / COSTA MESA / NEWPORT / IRVINE: NEWPORT BEACH; BALBOA 
WATER SERVICE WILL BE INTERRUPTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Beginning late Wednesday night and lasting until dawn Thursday, water will cut 
off to a portion of Balboa Peninsula while city workers reline a water main. 
</P>
<P>
 Pete Antista, Newport Beach utilities superintendent, said that residents who 
live between 8th Street and Island Avenue should plan to be without water from 
11 p.m. Wednesday to 5 a.m. Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Antista said some residents also will notice flakes of rust in their tap water 
while the project is underway. He said that people can safely drink that 
odd-colored water but should not use it to do laundry. 
</P>
<P>
 City workers, with the help of a hired contractor, will be relining a 16-inch 
water pipe that was installed in 1926 to serve the peninsula. Before the work 
begins, workers will go door-to-door to tell residents of the project. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents can expect a series of water interruptions in coming weeks but 
Antista is not sure when they will occur and for how long. 
</P>
</TEXT>
