<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / CENTRAL: WESTMINSTER; SCHOOL GETS $2,500 FROM MALL 
PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Westminster High School received $2,500 recently through the Cash for Class 
program sponsored by the Westminster Mall. 
</P>
<P>
 Eleven other high schools were given $250 to $2,000 under the program in which 
shoppers could trade their purchase receipts to earn points for their school. 
The program started Sept. 1 and ended Dec. 31. 
</P>
<P>
 The money will be used to provide scholarships, school equipment and 
computers. 
</P>
<P>
 A new program will start March 1 for 20 local public and private schools. 
</P>
<P>
 The other high schools that participated were Marina, $2,000; Ocean View, 
$1,500; Los Alamitos, $1,000; Pacifica, $750; Huntington Beach, $500, and Bolsa 
Grande, $500. 
</P>
<P>
 Also, Fountain Valley, $500; Edison, $500; Cypress, $250; Los Amigos, $250, 
and Rancho Alamitos, $250. 
</P>
</TEXT>
