<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / SADDLEBACK / SOUTH BEACH: LAGUNA HILLS; POLICE SEEK 
GUNMAN IN BAKERY ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies are looking for a robber who pistol-whipped an employee of 
a Laguna Hills Mall bakery early Monday morning and escaped with $2,700. 
</P>
<P>
 A Sheriff's Department spokesman said the gunman, wearing a ski mask, entered 
through the employee entrance of T.J. Cinnamons shortly after 5 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The man held a gun on the lone employee working at the bakery and demanded 
money, which the worker handed over in a bag. 
</P>
<P>
 However, the gunman demanded more. When shown an empty cash register he struck 
the baker on the head with his gun, then fled. 
</P>
<P>
 The employee complained of a lump on his head, but declined medical treatment 
and remained on the job. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies said the gunman is wanted on charges of armed robbery and assault. He 
was wearing dark pants, a gray sweater or sweat shirt and ski gloves. 
</P>
</TEXT>
