<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / CENTRAL: TUSTIN; DISTRICT TO RECONSIDER SCHOOL BOUNDARIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Public hearings will be held this month to consider changes in the Tustin 
Unified School District's middle school attendance boundaries because of the 
reopening of the Columbus Tustin Middle School. 
</P>
<P>
 After a $3.2-million renovation, Columbus Tustin will reopen for the 1994-95 
school year, becoming the fourth middle school in the district, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The attendance boundaries in some elementary schools also will be reconsidered 
because of changes in student enrollment, district administrators said. 
</P>
<P>
 Hearings will be held at Columbus Tustin Middle School, 13601 Browning Ave., 
on Wednesday; A.G. Currie Middle School, 1402 Sycamore Ave., on Feb. 15; and at 
Hewes Middle School, 13232 Hewes Ave., on Feb. 17. The hearings begin at 7 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Supt. David Andrews will discuss staff recommendations on boundary changes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
