<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OAK PARK; STARK, FREDERICKS OUT OF SUPERVISOR RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CARLOS V. LOZANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ronald Stark and J. Paul Fredericks, both members of the Oak Park Municipal 
Advisory Council, said Monday they are bowing out of the race for the Ventura 
County supervisorial seat being vacated by Maria VanderKolk. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'd love to try it," said Stark, who along with Fredericks had taken out 
nomination papers to run."But I just don't think it's realistic. . . . I would 
feel bad to have people contribute to a campaign that I know had no chance of 
winning." 
</P>
<P>
 Stark said he will support Thousand Oaks Councilman Frank Schillo in the June 
7 election. Fredericks said he will probably do the same. Both said they plan 
to consult with Schillo about his candidacy later this month. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to Schillo, three candidates remain in the race for the 
supervisorial seat representing the Conejo Valley and Port Hueneme. They are 
former Ventura County Supervisor Madge L. Schaefer, taxpayer advocate H. Jere 
Robings and corrections officer David Goodman. CARLOS V. LOZANO 
