<P>
4 MEN STABBED IN LA COLONIA; 2 HURT SERIOUSLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PATRICK McCARTNEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four men were stabbed on Cooper Road at McKinley Avenue in the east Oxnard 
neighborhood of La Colonia Monday evening in what police said was an apparent 
robbery. 
</P>
<P>
 The four Spanish-speaking victims appeared to be laborers and not associated 
with any gang, said Oxnard Police Sgt. Tim Combs. 
</P>
<P>
 All of the stabbing victims were hospitalized, and two were reported in 
serious condition. 
</P>
<P>
 Two of the victims were rushed to Ventura County Medical Center, where a 
nursing supervisor said one was in guarded condition and the other in serious 
condition. 
</P>
<P>
 A 23-year-old man taken to Pleasant Valley Hospital was reported in stable 
condition with three stab wounds but no major loss of blood. 
</P>
<P>
 The fourth victim was transported to St. John's Regional Medical Center and 
underwent surgery for abdominal wounds. A nursing supervisor said his condition 
was serious. 
</P>
<P>
 The stabbings were reported to police around 7:30 p.m., but no suspects were 
immediately identified. An investigation is continuing, Combs said. PATRICK 
McCARTNEY 
