EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; CANDIDATE WILL HOLD VOTER OPEN HOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CARLOS V. LOZANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mark Boos Benhard, who plans to announce his candidacy for the congressional 
seat representing Thousand Oaks next week, will hold a voter open-house meeting 
on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents are invited to attend the 8 p.m. meeting at the home of Dr. Paul and 
Teri Reisser at 1885 Montgomery Road.Those interested should call (805) 
379-4520 or (818) 707-0264. 
</P>
<P>
 Benhard, 29, of Agoura, is one of three Republicans expected to battle for the 
nomination to oppose Democratic Rep. Anthony C. Beilenson, whose 24th District 
includes Malibu and part of the San Fernando Valley. Benhard, who has already 
opened a campaign office in Woodland Hills, said he plans to formally announce 
his candidacy within the next two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Hammer, a Newbury Park banking consultant, is the only officially 
declared Republican candidate in the congressional race. Richard Sybert, a 
former aide to Gov. Pete Wilson, is also expected to enter the race. 
</P>
<P>
 So far, no Democratic candidates have stepped forward to challenge Beilenson, 
who is seeking his 10th term in Congress. 
</P>
<P>
 Benhard said he plans to hold a series of open house meetings over the next 
several months to discuss his campaign to fight crime and reduce taxes. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've already set up 50 house meetings," he said. "We hope to hold 100. It's 
a way of taking our message directly to the public." CARLOS V. LOZANO 
