<P>
 A fire caused by an electric blanket nearly destroyed a Ventura house Monday 
afternoon, but none of the six people at home were injured, said a spokesman 
for the Ventura County Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
 The house, located at 5382 Norway Drive, was engulfed in flames within seconds 
after a short circuit occurred in one of the bedroom's electrical blankets. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire, which was put out within 25 minutes, caused more than $35,000 in 
damage and left the house uninhabitable, officials said. CHRISTINA LIMA 
