<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: MATTHEWS STUDIO EQUIPMENT PROFIT UP 19% IN 1ST QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Matthews Studio Equipment Group, a Burbank supplier of camera and lighting 
equipment to the entertainment industry, reported that its fiscal first-quarter 
earnings rose 19% from a year earlier while revenue remained flat. 
</P>
<P>
 In the three months that ended Dec. 31, Matthews had a profit of $482,000, up 
from $405,000 the year before. In its latest quarter revenue totaled $6.56 
million, compared to $6.5 million a year before. 
</P>
<P>
 Matthews said the latest results included a 33% increase in rental income and 
a $200,000 reduction in operating expenses over the first quarter a year ago. 
