<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: ASTRO SCIENCES' PROFIT DOWN 80% IN 3RD QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Astro Sciences Corp., a Chatsworth manufacturer of computer networking 
products, reported an 80% plunge in its profit for its fiscal third quarter 
ended Dec. 31.The drop resulted from increased research, development and 
marketing expenses, the manufacturer said. 
</P>
<P>
 The company's net income of $75,836 was down from a $379,867 profit a year 
before. Its revenue fell 5%, to $3.61 million from $3.81 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For the nine months, Astro Sciences earned $50,091, down 93% from $676,558 in 
net income in the year-ago period. Revenue totaled $9.02 million, up 3% from 
$8.78 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
