<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: MEDGROUP REPORTS LOSS IN 3RD QUARTER OF $474,890 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 MedGroup Inc., an Encino supplier of medical products, posted a $474,890 net 
loss for its fiscal third quarter, contrasted with a profit of $24,048 a year 
earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 Revenue dipped 2% in the quarter that ended Dec. 31 to $969,749 from $991,323 
a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 Medgroup blamed its net loss largely on the cost of launching several new 
products. The company expects two of those products, a car seat for the 
disabled and a system for shipping temperature-sensitive medical supplies, to 
begin producing revenue later this quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 During the third quarter, Med group also said it absorbed a one-time loss of 
$381,000 from the 1992 sale of its physical therapy clinics because the buyer 
defaulted on its note. 
</P>
<P>
 For the nine months, Medgroup's net loss nearly doubled to $422,470 from 
$224,933 for the same period last year. Revenue fell 31% to $2.74 million from 
$3.98 million a year earlier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
