<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: PERCEPTRONICS WINS CONTRACTS FOR $950,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Perceptronics Inc., a Woodland Hills maker of computer-based simulation 
systems for commercial and military training, said it received two contracts 
totaling $950,000 from the Advanced Research Projects Agency. 
</P>
<P>
 One contract is for $700,000 and calls on Perceptronics to modify an existing 
contract being administered by the U. S. Army Missile Command of Huntsville, 
Ala. The other award, for $250,000, is part of the agency's small business 
innovative research program. 
</P>
