<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 School quake information -- Sunday's editions inaccurately reported the Los 
Angeles Unified School District's telephone number that was overwhelmed by 
calls for earthquake information. The correct number is (213) 625-4000. 
</P>
<P>
 In the same story, a paragraph that clarified the quake response of KLCS, the 
district's TV station, was deleted. Beginning two days after the quake, the 
station interrupted regular programming to air press conferences and Board of 
Education meetings and to carry the Federal Emergency Management Agency's 
recovery channel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
