<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Insurance ratings -- In a Jan. 25 story The Times reported that because of 
about $30 million in earthquake damage claims, Associated International 
Insurance Co. in Woodland Hills was in jeopardy of a change in its insurance 
rating. To clarify, A. M. Best, a leading insurance ratings service, is now 
reviewing the financial condition of many Southern California insurance 
companies that face earthquake damage claims. But A. M. Best has not yet 
concluded its ratings review for those companies. 
</P>
